'''Google圖書'''（{{lang-en|Google Books}}）是一個由Google研發的搜尋工具，它可以自[[Google|Google]]所掃描、經由[[光學字符識別|光學字符識別]]（OCR）、儲存的數位化數據庫中搜尋資料。此服務於[[2004年10月|2004年10月]]在[[法蘭克福書展|法蘭克福書展]]发布，命名為'''Google Print'''。當用戶使用關鍵字搜尋，Google圖書搜尋的結果索引會顯示在Google網路搜尋服務的上方。用戶還可以在Google圖書搜尋搜尋書籍。點擊Google圖書搜尋的結果索引打開頁面，使用戶可以查看書籍中的頁面以及內容相關的廣告，鏈接到出版商的網站和書店。Google以限制網頁的瀏覽數量，來阻止書籍被列印和保護文字內容的複製版權，並追蹤用戶使用記錄，作為通過各種准入限制和保障措施的依據。<ref>{{Cite web |title=Google's Cookie and Hacking Google Print |url=http://www.kuro5hin.org/story/2005/3/7/95844/59875 |author=Greg Duffy |date=March 2005 |work=[[Kuro5hin|Kuro5hin]] |accessdate=2008-12-04 |archive-date=2021-01-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126201516/http://www.kuro5hin.org/story/2005/3/7/95844/59875 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 

Google圖書搜尋允許[[公有領域|公有領域]]的作品和內容，免費全文瀏覽，並提供[[PDF|PDF]]的格式下載。對於在美國境外的用戶，Google必須確保其沒有觸犯到用戶所在國家的法律，根據Google圖書搜尋支援小組的成員說法：「一本書是否屬於公有領域往往是一個棘手的法律問題，我們會謹慎處理，直到我們確定本書已進入公有領域。」<ref>{{Cite web |title=From the mail bag: Public domain books and downloads |url=http://booksearch.blogspot.com/2006/11/from-mail-bag-public-domain-books-and.html |author=Ryan Sands |date=2006年11月9日 |format=[[blog|blog]] |work=Inside Google Book Search |accessdate=2008-12-04 |archive-date=2011-07-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721220053/http://booksearch.blogspot.com/2006/11/from-mail-bag-public-domain-books-and.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

關於掃描方面，許多書籍使用Elphel 323相機掃描，這種相機每小時可以照1,000頁。<ref name="nyt">{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2006/05/14/magazine/14publishing.html?_r=1&oref=slogin&pagewanted=all |title=Scan This Book! |last=Kelly |first=Kevin |date=2006年5月14日 |publisher=[[New_York_Times_Magazine|New York Times Magazine]] |accessdate=2008-03-07 |quote=When Google announced in December 2004 that it would digitally scan the books of five major research libraries to make their contents searchable, the promise of a universal library was resurrected. ... From the days of Sumerian clay tablets till now, humans have "published" at least 32 million books, 750 million articles and essays, 25 million songs, 500 million images, 500,000 movies, 3 million videos, TV shows and short films and 100 billion public Web pages. |archive-date=2021-01-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125090149/http://www.nytimes.com/2006/05/14/magazine/14publishing.html?_r=1&pagewanted=all&oref=slogin |dead-url=no }}</ref>

而Google的這個計畫受到極大稱讚，因為它可能成為前所未有、全球最大的網上主體的人類知識，<ref>{{cite news |first=Kevin |last=Bergquist |title=Google project promotes public good |url=http://www.umich.edu/~urecord/0506/Feb13_06/02.shtml |work=The University Record |publisher=[[University_of_Michigan|University of Michigan]] |date=2006年2月13日 |accessdate=2007-04-11 |archive-date=2007-10-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071012194543/http://umich.edu/~urecord/0506/Feb13_06/02.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Is This the Renaissance or the Dark Ages? |last=Pace |first=Andrew K. |url=http://www.ala.org/ala/alonline/techspeaking/2006columnsa/techJan2006.cfm |work=American Libraries |publisher=[[American_Library_Association|American Library Association]] |accessdate=2007-04-11 |quote=Google made instant e-book believers out of skeptics even though 10 years of e-book evangelism among librarians had barely made progress. |date=January 2006 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070403083647/http://www.ala.org/ala/alonline/techspeaking/2006columnsa/techJan2006.cfm |archivedate=2007-04-03 }}</ref>但它仍有著有關侵犯版權上的批評。<ref name=LAWSUITS />

== 計畫目的 ==
Google圖書掃描圖書的目的，并不是給人類閲讀，而是用於訓練[[人工智能|人工智能]]<ref>{{cite book |last1=Dyson |first1=George |title=Turing's Cathedral: The Origins of the Digital Universe |date=2012 |publisher=Knopf Doubleday Publishing Group |isbn=978-0-307-90706-6 |pages=312-313 |url=https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=9nvfmUS03c4C |language=en |access-date=2020-10-18 |archive-date=2020-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201114012319/https://books.google.com.hk/books?id=9nvfmUS03c4C |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

== 掃描數量 ==
Google曾表示，他們目前一天可掃描三千本書籍。到2007年3月為止，Google已經數位化100萬本圖書。Google拒絕透露項目開支，但《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》在2008年時估算其花費了約500萬美元。<ref name="NYT2007">{{Cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/03/10/business/yourmoney/11archive.html |title=History, Digitized (and Abridged) |last=Hafner |first=Katie |date=March 10, 2007 |publisher=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]] |accessdate=2008-04-10 |quote=Google, on its own, is digitizing books at the Library of Congress, which has its hands full with other items. ... In its quest to scan every one of the tens of millions of books ever published, Google has already digitized one million volumes. Google refuses to say how much it has spent on the venture so far, but outside experts estimate the figure at at least US$5 million. The company has also been scanning and indexing academic journals to make them searchable, and is working with the Patent Office to digitize thousands of patents dating back to 1790. |archive-date=2020-11-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201122082151/https://www.nytimes.com/2007/03/10/business/yourmoney/11archive.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>在2008年10月28日Google說，通過此项服务，他們有700萬本的圖書被搜索，其中包括掃描的20,000個出版商的合作夥伴<ref>{{Cite web |title=New Chapter |url=http://googleblog.blogspot.com/2008/10/new-chapter-for-google-book-search.html |accessdate=2008-10-29 |publisher=[[Google|Google]] |archive-date=2020-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109021553/https://googleblog.blogspot.com/2008/10/new-chapter-for-google-book-search.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在這700萬冊圖書当中，有100萬本在出版商正式授權下提供“完全預覽”服務，另外100萬屬於在公有領域，其餘500萬是絕版或商用。<ref name="pcworldscan">{{Cite news |url=http://www.pcworld.com/businesscenter/article/153085/in_google_book_settlement_business_trumps_ideals.html |title=In Google Book Settlement, Business Trumps Ideals |date=October 28, 2008 |work=[[PC_World|PC World]] |accessdate=2008-10-31 |quote=Of the 7 million books Google has scanned, 1 million are in full preview mode as part of formal publisher agreements. Another 1 million are public domain works. |archive-date=2011-12-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111229201430/http://www.pcworld.com/businesscenter/article/153085/in_google_book_settlement_business_trumps_ideals.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 競爭 ==
* [[微軟|微軟]]在2006年開發了一個類似的計畫，名叫{{link-en|Live Search Books|Live Search Books}}。它持續進行了一段时间，直到2008年5月取消<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.theage.com.au/news/biztech/microsoft-starts-online-library-in-challenge-to-google-books/2006/12/07/1165081127665.html |title=Microsoft starts online library in challenge to Google Books |work=[[AFP|AFP]] |accessdate=2008-11-24 |quote=Microsoft launched an online library in a move that pits the world's biggest software company against Google's controversial project to digitize the world's books. |archive-date=2018-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618125647/https://www.theage.com.au/news/biztech/microsoft-starts-online-library-in-challenge-to-google-books/2006/12/07/1165081127665.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。所有的Live Search Books的資料，現已存在[[Internet_Archive|Internet Archive]]。Internet Archive是非營利性的，它是繼Google之後第二大圖書掃描計畫。截至2008年11月已有超過100萬全文公有領域的作品被掃描上網。
* [[歐洲數位圖書館|Europeana]]主宰約300萬份的數位物件，其中包括影像、照片、繪畫、音頻、地圖、手稿、印刷書籍、報紙等，這些檔案超過一千項是由[[歐盟|歐盟]]自過去兩千年的歐洲歷史搜集而成的。<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://blog.wired.com/business/2008/11/eu-launches-mas.html |title=Europe's Answer to Google Book Search Crashes on Day 1 |date=2008 |work=[[Wired|Wired]] |accessdate=2008-11-24 |archive-date=2009-04-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090416002826/http://blog.wired.com/business/2008/11/eu-launches-mas.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

